<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
Gate 2 — recursive="true", out-of-coverage at ca:country → request forwarded
through the full LoST tree to the Forest Guide, which returns <notFound>.

REQUIRES RUNNING PARENT LVF AND FOREST GUIDE: LVF_PARENT_URI must point to a
reachable parent LVF, which must in turn be configured with LVF_PARENT_URI
pointing to a reachable Forest Guide. This test will fail with a serverTimeout
or serverError outcome if either the parent or the Forest Guide is unreachable.
The golden file reflects the live Forest Guide response and will not match if
the upstream tree is unavailable.

country=CA does not match any provisioned GIS record on this node (all records
have country=US). Gate 2 fires stop-on-first-invalid at ca:country. The civic
coverage lookup for CA/ND/Burleigh County finds no match — this LVF has no
coverage for country=CA. Because recursive="true" and a parent is configured,
the child forwards the request to the parent LVF.

The parent LVF similarly holds no coverage for country=CA and forwards the
request to the Forest Guide. The Forest Guide holds no registered coverage
region matching country=CA and returns <notFound>.

The full chain traversed: child LVF → parent LVF → Forest Guide.
-->
<findService xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:lost1" validateLocation="true" recursive="true">
  <location id="L1" profile="civic">
    <civicAddress xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:pidf:geopriv10:civicAddr" xml:lang="en-US">
      <country>CA</country>
      <A1>ND</A1>
      <A2>Burleigh County</A2>
      <A3>Bismarck</A3>
      <RD>State</RD>
      <STS>Street</STS>
      <HNO>3401</HNO>
      <PC>58503</PC>
    </civicAddress>
  </location>
  <service>urn:service:sos</service>
</findService>
